Homework Explanations

homework3

problem1 : the 6th question

Answer: substitutes.

Because the price of good2 rises, p1 increases with q1 = 1000-10p1 +

5p2 + 2I, then q1 increases, which is in good agreement with good1 and

good2 being substitutes. If it is complementary, then p2 increased, q1

should be reduced.

problem2: the 3th question

Answer：We cannot conclude definitely whether food is normal or inferior.

Because we draw the horizontal axis of the data as income, the

vertical axis for food expenditure. According to the definition of

normal good, when the income increases, the number of purchased goods

should be increased. What we can draw from the picture is that when

income increases, food expenditure increases, ie P * Q. When the good

is inferior, it is also possible to draw such an image (for example,

the quantity of Inferior good has not changed and its price has

risen), so we can not judge it.

problem3: the 6th question

Stressed a bit When studying the relationship between oil and corn price

changes, the need to control other factors unchanged. Otherwise, other

factors, such as income changes, can have an impact on the result.
